SIMPLE: dehort
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dehort
<hw>De*hort"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Dehorted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Dehorting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>dehortari</ets>;
<ets>de-</ets> + <ets>hortari</ets> to urge, exhort.]</ety> <def>To urge
to abstain or refrain; to dissuade.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The apostles vehemently <qex>dehort</qex> us from unbelief.</q>
<rj><qau>Bp. Ward.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>⟦ldquo⟧Exhort⟦rdquo⟧ remains, but <qex>dehort</qex>, a word whose
place neither ⟦ldquo⟧dissuade⟦rdquo⟧ nor any other exactly supplies, has
escaped us.</q> <rj><qau>Trench.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dehortation</ent>⟦br⟧
